'''Milton Johns''' is a British actor who portrayed [[Bewil]], an [[Imperial officer]], in [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']]. He has two lines in the Carbon Freezing chaimber, the first of which, "Lord Vader. Ship approaching, X-wing class.", Johns delivers in his own voice. However, for the second line, "Skywalker has just landed, m'lord.", his voice was dubbed by a more American sounding actor.

He is best known to sci-fi fans for appearing in [[Wikipedia:Doctor Who|''Doctor Who'']] in the stories [[Wikipedia:The Enemy of the World|''The Enemy of the World'']] (1967-68), [[Wikipedia:The Android Invasion|''The Android Invasion'']] (1975) and [[Wikipedia:The Invasion of Time|''The Invasion of Time'']] (1978).

